---
layout: layouts/component-demo.njk
title: Progress
description: a horizontal progress bar showing completion
---

{% from "components/progress/macro.njk" import progress %}

<h2>Determinate</h2>
<p>The <code>&lt;progress&gt;</code> element exposes
  <code>role="progressbar"</code> and its value natively, so no
  extra ARIA is needed when value and max are set.</p>

<p>40% complete:</p>
{{ progress({ value: 40, max: 100, label: "Upload progress" }) }}

<p>75% complete:</p>
{{ progress({ value: 75, max: 100, label: "Download progress" }) }}

<h2>Custom max</h2>
<p>Step 3 of 5:</p>
{{ progress({ value: 3, max: 5, label: "Application progress" }) }}

<h2>Indeterminate</h2>
<p>Omit <code>value</code> to show an indeterminate state (browser-
  drawn barber-pole stripes).</p>
{{ progress({ label: "Loading" }) }}

<h2>Linked heading</h2>
<h3 id="deploy-title">Deployment progress</h3>
{{ progress({
  value: 90,
  max: 100,
  labelledBy: "deploy-title"
}) }}
